---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Threadmark for Mid-Market Brands"
	description="Audit-ready compliance infrastructure for growing brands. Centralise product compliance records, track changes, and export documentation on demand."
>
	<!-- Hero -->
	<section class="hero">
		<h1>Your product compliance data should be audit-ready today, not next quarter.</h1>
		<p class="hero-sub">
			Growing brands need compliance infrastructure that keeps pace. Threadmark gives
			your compliance and operations teams a single system of record for product data,
			certifications, and audit documentation.
		</p>
		<div class="hero-cta">
			<a href={siteConfig.calendarUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary">Book a call</a>
			<a href="#waitlist" class="btn btn-secondary">Join the waitlist</a>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Use cases -->
	<section class="use-cases-section">
		<h2>Built for how compliance teams actually work</h2>
		<ul class="use-cases">
			<li>
				<strong>Audit preparation</strong>
				<p>
					Pull a complete compliance report for any product or date range. Every field
					change is tracked, so you can show exactly what changed and when.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Supplier documentation</strong>
				<p>
					Attach certifications, test reports, and supplier references directly to
					products. No more digging through email threads.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Cross-team visibility</strong>
				<p>
					Role-based access means compliance officers, operations managers, and product
					teams each see what they need — nothing more, nothing less.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Customer transparency</strong>
				<p>
					Generate public compliance pages with QR codes so customers and retail
					partners can verify product data themselves.
				</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<!-- Capabilities -->
	<section class="capabilities-section">
		<h2>What you get</h2>
		<ul class="capabilities">
			<li>
				<strong>Full audit trail</strong>
				<span>Every compliance field change is logged with timestamp, user, and previous value.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Versioned exports</strong>
				<span>Generate JSON or PDF compliance reports with built-in versioning for traceability.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Role-based access control</strong>
				<span>Admin, editor, and viewer roles with per-store data isolation.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Structured compliance data</strong>
				<span>Validated fields for materials composition, certifications, and product documentation.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Automatic product sync</strong>
				<span>Products sync from your Shopify catalogue via webhooks. No manual imports.</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Compliance status dashboard</strong>
				<span>See which products have complete records and which need attention.</span>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<!-- Not a fit -->
	<section class="not-a-fit-section">
		<h2>Threadmark might not be the right fit if&hellip;</h2>
		<ul class="not-a-fit">
			<li>You need automated regulatory compliance checking or legal interpretation.</li>
			<li>You need supply chain tracking beyond supplier references and certifications.</li>
			<li>You sell on multiple marketplaces (Amazon, eBay) and need unified compliance across all of them.</li>
			<li>You need AI-powered auto-categorisation or predictive compliance tools.</li>
			<li>You're looking for tax calculation, customs, or logistics integrations.</li>
		</ul>
		<p class="not-a-fit-note">
			Threadmark focuses on compliance data management and export. Regulatory
			interpretation and legal compliance validation remain your responsibility.
		</p>
	</section>

	<!-- FAQ -->
	<section class="faq-section">
		<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
		<dl class="faq-list">
			<div class="faq-item">
				<dt>How is this different from a spreadsheet or shared drive?</dt>
				<dd>
					Threadmark provides structured, validated fields with a full audit trail.
					Every change is tracked. Exports are versioned. Access is role-controlled.
					Spreadsheets can't do any of that reliably at scale.
				</dd>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<dt>What size catalogue does this support?</dt>
				<dd>
					Threadmark is designed for brands with 50–200+ SKUs. If you have a larger
					catalogue, get in touch and we'll discuss the right approach.
				</dd>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<dt>Does Threadmark replace our compliance team?</dt>
				<dd>
					No. Threadmark is a tool for your compliance team, not a replacement. It
					organises and exports the data they already manage — it doesn't make
					regulatory decisions.
				</dd>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<dt>Can multiple team members use it?</dt>
				<dd>
					Yes. Role-based access control supports admin, editor, and viewer roles.
					All actions are logged in the audit trail.
				</dd>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<dt>What export formats are available?</dt>
				<dd>
					JSON and PDF, both with versioning. Exports include full compliance data
					for the products and date range you select.
				</dd>
			</div>
		</dl>
	</section>

	<!-- Contact / Waitlist -->
	<section class="waitlist-section" id="waitlist">
		<h2>Get in touch</h2>
		<p>
			Book a call to discuss how Threadmark fits your compliance workflow,
			or join the waitlist for early access.
		</p>
		<form
			name="waitlist-mid-market"
			method="POST"
			data-netlify="true"
			action="/thanks"
		>
			<input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="waitlist-mid-market" />
			<div class="form-fields">
				<div class="form-field">
					<label for="name-mm">Name</label>
					<input
						type="text"
						id="name-mm"
						name="name"
						required
						placeholder="Your name"
						autocomplete="name"
					/>
				</div>
				<div class="form-field">
					<label for="email-mm">Work email</label>
					<input
						type="email"
						id="email-mm"
						name="email"
						required
						placeholder="you@company.com"
						autocomplete="email"
					/>
				</div>
				<div class="form-field">
					<label for="company-mm">Company</label>
					<input
						type="text"
						id="company-mm"
						name="company"
						placeholder="Company name"
						autocomplete="organization"
					/>
				</div>
			</div>
			<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Join waitlist</button>
			<p class="form-notice">We'll only use your information to contact you about Threadmark. <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></p>
		</form>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	/* Hero */
	.hero {
		padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
		max-width: 40rem;
	}

	.hero h1 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		line-height: 1.2;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}

	.hero-sub {
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
		color: #4b5563;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.hero-cta {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.btn {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
		min-height: 2.75rem;
		border-radius: 0.375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		text-decoration: none;
		text-align: center;
		transition: background-color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
	}

	.btn-primary {
		background: #111827;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.btn-primary:hover {
		background: #1f2937;
	}

	.btn-secondary {
		background: #fff;
		color: #111827;
		border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
	}

	.btn-secondary:hover {
		border-color: #111827;
	}

	/* Use cases */
	.use-cases-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.use-cases-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.use-cases {
		list-style: none;
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.use-cases li strong {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
	}

	.use-cases li p {
		color: #4b5563;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
	}

	/* Capabilities */
	.capabilities-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.capabilities-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.capabilities {
		list-style: none;
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.25rem;
	}

	.capabilities li {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.25rem;
	}

	.capabilities strong {
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
	}

	.capabilities span {
		color: #6b7280;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
	}

	/* Not a fit */
	.not-a-fit-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.not-a-fit-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.not-a-fit {
		list-style: none;
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.625rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.not-a-fit li {
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		background: #fef2f2;
		border-radius: 0.375rem;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
		color: #991b1b;
	}

	.not-a-fit-note {
		color: #6b7280;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	/* FAQ */
	.faq-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.faq-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.faq-list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.25rem;
	}

	.faq-item dt {
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
	}

	.faq-item dd {
		color: #4b5563;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
	}

	/* Waitlist */
	.waitlist-section {
		padding: 3rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
	}

	.waitlist-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.waitlist-section p {
		color: #6b7280;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.form-fields {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1rem;
		max-width: 28rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}

	.form-field label {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
	}

	.form-field input {
		width: 100%;
		min-height: 2.75rem;
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
		border-radius: 0.375rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-family: inherit;
	}

	.form-notice {
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		color: #6b7280;
	}

	.form-notice a {
		color: #6b7280;
		text-decoration: underline;
	}

	.form-notice a:hover {
		color: #111827;
	}

	.form-field input:focus {
		outline: 2px solid #111827;
		outline-offset: -1px;
		border-color: transparent;
	}

	@media (min-width: 640px) {
		.hero h1 {
			font-size: 2.5rem;
		}

		.use-cases {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		}

		.capabilities {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
